    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH1a0938-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T22:29:07.349+09:00">As for the wise men, who address themselves to the task of governing the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:03:35.278+09:00">they must certainly know where the disorder arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:07:23.7+09:00">then they are able to govern it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:14:13.007+09:00">then they are not able to govern it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:18:19.838+09:00">Things are the same as with a doctor who wants to cure someone else's disease.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:19:35.181+09:00">He must certainly know where the disease arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:19:48.467+09:00">then he is able to cure it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:20:10.095+09:00">If he does not know where the disease arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:20:21.811+09:00">then he is not able to cure it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:22:01.721+09:00">How, then, should it be any different for those who govern disorder?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:22:38.617+09:00">They must certainly know where the disorder arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:22:44.838+09:00">then they are able to govern it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:22:56.11+09:00">If they do not know where the disorder arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:23:04.426+09:00">then they are not able to govern it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:46:45.889+09:00">If they do not know where the disorder arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:47:33.582+09:00">As for the wise men, who address themselves to the task of governing the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:50:48.389+09:00">they inevitably have to investigate where the disorder arises from.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:52:32.463+09:00">Let us try to investigate where the disorder arises from.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="guest" modified="2019-11-18T18:51:03.155+09:00">                                    It arises from the fact that people do not spare each other.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:58:30.269+09:00">is something called disorder.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T19:03:49.023+09:00">That subject and son do not serve their ruler or father in piety</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T18:53:40.023+09:00">                                    Since a son spares himself and not his father,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:59:59.628+09:00">he therefore harms his father and benefits himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T18:53:33.876+09:00">                                    Since a younger brother spares himself and not his older brother,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T19:01:52.828+09:00">he therefore harms his older brother and benefits himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="guest" modified="2019-11-18T18:52:39.63+09:00">                                    Since a subject spares himself and not his ruler,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T19:03:59.192+09:00">he therefore harms his ruler and benefits himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T18:55:41.701+09:00">This is something that is called disorder.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-19T22:24:45.035+09:00">                                    Even if the father does not show parental care for his son,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-19T22:24:54.106+09:00">                                    the elder brother does not show parental care for his younger brother,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-19T22:24:59.886+09:00">                                    the ruler does not show parental care for his subject,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:02:08.834+09:00">then this is also something that the world calls disorder.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:02:50.284+09:00">Since the father [actually] spares himself</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:02:55.207+09:00">and not his son,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:03:31.063+09:00">he therefore harms his son and benefits himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:04:23.551+09:00">Since the elder brother [actually] spares himself</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:04:33.109+09:00">and not his younger brother,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:04:45.78+09:00">he therefore harms his younger brother and benefits himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:05:02.879+09:00">Since the ruler [actually] spares himself</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:05:06.161+09:00">and not his subject,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:05:14.44+09:00">he therefore harms his subject and benefits himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:05:52.863+09:00">Why is this the case?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:06:36.319+09:00">All this is due to the fact that people do not spare each other.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:08:46.996+09:00">Even with those who are acting as robbers and murderers in the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:08:50.071+09:00">it is the same.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:09:20.851+09:00">A robber spares his [own] house,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:09:44.502+09:00">but not others' houses,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:10:44.047+09:00">therefore he robs others' houses in order to benefit his [own] house.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:11:11.863+09:00">A murderer spares his [own] body,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:11:31.075+09:00">but not [that of] others,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:11:53.585+09:00">therefore he murders others in order to benefit his own.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:12:09.71+09:00">Why is this the case?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:12:30.05+09:00">All this is due to the fact that people do not spare each other.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:15:22.622+09:00">Even with the great ones who bring their families into disorder mutually or with the rulers who attack their countries mutually,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-18T19:15:27.027+09:00">it is the same.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
